Queries live data from the Halliburton Sites and Costs Summary Power BI semantic model. Use when users ask about sites, NBV, ROU, contracts, costs, billing, facilities, PSL, or risk.

Key measures (exact names for DAX):
[Count_Expired_Contract], [Count_Expired_Contract_No_SR], [Count_ActContr_on_TermSite], [Count_ActLeasedSite_No_Contract], [Count_Contract], [Count_Site], [Count_Presentation], [Value_NBV], [Value_ROU], [Value_Building], [Value_Land]

Tables: 'CurMonData' (main), 'Billing File' (costs), 'Need Attention' (facilities), 'CurMonNBV' (NBV), 'REISPO' (occupancy), 'ZFAF' (assets)

DAX examples:
Overview: EVALUATE ROW("Expired",CALCULATE([Count_Expired_Contract]),"NBV",CALCULATE([Value_NBV]),"ROU",CALCULATE([Value_ROU]))
Billing: EVALUATE SUMMARIZECOLUMNS('Billing File'[Facility Name],'Billing File'[PSL Name],"Cost",SUM('Billing File'[Allocated USD]))
NBV: EVALUATE FILTER('Need Attention','Need Attention'[City]="Comodoro Rivadavia")
PSL: EVALUATE CALCULATETABLE(SUMMARIZECOLUMNS('Billing File'[Region],'Billing File'[Facility Name]),'Billing File'[PSL Name]="Cementing")
